subject: Re: [junit] JUnit Report Problem
msgSnippet: ... I think you may require a later version of ANT. I don t think 1.6.5 or earlier supports JUnit 4.x. Cheers, James
messageBody:
On 27/11/2007, m_giriprasad <m_giriprasad@...> wrote:
>
> Hi All,
>
> I am using JUnit 4.0 to test my code. when I execute my JUnit using ant
> script(Ant ver - 1.6.x). The Junits get executed and the report too
> gets genereted.
>
> When I browse through the report, I see that the pass and Fail % are
> displayed. However all my test methods are displayed as unknown.
>
> Why are the methods displayed as unknown?

I think you may require a later version of ANT. I don't think 1.6.5 or
earlier supports JUnit 4.x.

Cheers,

James
